In this example, for an exercise, do the following

1) get a fixed grid solution
2) release down stream meniscus

3) determine the volume of the mesh. Either run one iteration 
with the AC command turned on (i.e., just change number of ACs to -1
or uncomment the AC card, whichever way you want to do it.

Then you can use -n 1 and -r 0.0 as switches for a goma run.  The volume
of the mesh will be output at the end of the run (VC) or as a global variable
in out.exoII.  viz.   

ncdump out.exoII | more
(searchfor val  and you will se val_glob_var and the 5th number is the volume.)


